                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2170a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department feels it is unnecessary to hold Mena indefinitely, although the
                    Canal Courts have decided his detention legal, unless there are reasons for
                    believing him still dangerous to the future peace of Nicaragua. Report your
                    views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
